-- Metro Said to Sell 500 Million Euros of Seven-Year Bonds
-- B y   B e n   M a r t i n
-- 2012-02-22T09:08:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-22/metro-said-to-sell-500-million-euros-of-seven-year-bonds.html
Metro AG (MEO)  is offering 500 million
euros of seven-year bonds, according to a banker with knowledge
of the transaction.  The bonds may be priced to yield about 155 basis points
more than the benchmark mid-swap rate, the banker said.
Commerzbank AG, ING Groep NV,  Banco Santander SA (SAN)  and  UniCredit
SpA (UCG)  are managing the deal.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ben Martin at 
 bmartin38@bloomberg.net  